---
import { Markdown } from 'astro/components';
---
<article>
    <div class="banner">
    <h2>This is an Astro component</h2>
    <p>It's imported into the <code>index.astro</code> page</p>
    <p>As a component I live in the components folder.</p>
    </div>

    <section>
        <Markdown>
            ## Is this Markdown?

            Yup! Here comes some code in tripple backticks: 

            ```
            <Markdown>
                ## It really is markdown?
            </Markdown>
            ```
            - It's really cool.
            - You can even put `.md` -files in the pages folder and link to them.
            [This is a markdown link to a markdown page](../about)
        </Markdown>
    </section>
    
</article>

<style>
    article {
        padding-top: 2em;
        line-height: 1.5;
        border: solid 1px grey;
        margin-bottom: 2em;
    }
    section {
        margin-top: 2em;
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        gap: 1em;
        max-width: 70ch;
    }

    .banner {
        text-align: center;
        font-size: 1.2rem;
        background: var(--color-light);
        padding: 1em 1.5em;
        padding-left: 0.75em;
        border-radius: 4px;
    }

    pre,
    code {
        font-family: var(--font-mono);
        background: var(--color-light);
        border-radius: 4px;
    }

    pre {
        padding: 1em 1.5em;
    }

    .tree {
        line-height: 1.2;
    }

    code:not(.tree) {
        padding: 0.125em;
        margin: 0 -0.125em;
    }
</style>
